OL,6,FJudge Sophie McKone handed Okoronta a
OL,7,F10-year sentence, with an extended
OL,8,Flicence period of three years.
OL,10,FShe told him: "You knew she was a
OL,11,Fvulnerable person, miles from where
OL,12,Fshe needed to be. You knew she needed
OL,13,Fto get to Bradford. She was 17 and had
OL,14,Flittle money and her phone was dead.
OL,15,FI'm satisfied when you asked her to
OL,16,Fshare a taxi you formulated a plan to
OL,17,Fget her back to your address where you
OL,18,Fcould rape her.
